rely on DADA2: reads are dereplicated with
\href{https://github.com/torognes/vsearch}{vsearch} (\code{--derep_fulllength}),
pooled across samples, clustered with
\href{https://github.com/torognes/swarm}{SWARM} (default) or vsearch
(\code{--cluster_size}), and the per-sample cluster abundances are assembled
into a \code{\link[phyloseq:phyloseq-class]{phyloseq::phyloseq-class()}} object with an \code{otu_table} and the
representative (seed/centroid) sequence of each OTU in the \code{refseq} slot.

This complements \code{\link[=asv2otu]{asv2otu()}}, which post-clusters ASVs already stored in
a phyloseq object: \code{reads2otu()} starts one step earlier, directly from
sequence files or a vector of DNA sequences.
